WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.555 --> 00:00:04.555
Narrator: 44 years in an institution

00:00:04.750 --> 00:00:07.200
Unable to read or write

00:00:07.666 --> 00:00:11.555
No family…no place in society

00:00:11.555 --> 00:00:15.750
An unlikely friendship changed his life forever

00:00:15.750 --> 00:00:21.666
Barry Morrow: As I walked toward him, his eyes lit 
up, he jumped to his feet, he thrust out his hand

00:00:21.666 --> 00:00:25.600
and he said, “Hey Buddy, my name’s Bill”.

00:00:25.600 --> 00:00:31.480
Narrator: His story inspired millions. 
Now meet the real Bill Sackter

00:00:31.480 --> 00:00:36.333
Bill Sackter: Hey, it’s getting cold…
You should put that wig on.

00:00:36.333 --> 00:00:39.900
Denny Sundlie; We’ve got Wild Bill over here, 
so let’s give him a great big hand,

00:00:39.900 --> 00:00:42.015
and get him up here to play a song for you.

00:00:47.250 --> 00:00:50.750
Band (singing): In heaven there is no beer,

00:00:50.750 --> 00:00:53.350
That’s why Bill drinks it here

00:00:53.350 --> 00:00:58.050
Bill: We did a little rock-n-roll 
and shaked the boogeys, and we had fun.

00:00:58.050 --> 00:01:01.650
Narrator: All he needed was 
a little help from his friends.

00:01:01.650 --> 00:01:05.500
Tom Walz: He should have been a bartender, 
you know, so being an entrepreneur

00:01:05.500 --> 00:01:08.600
of a little coffee shop was 
the next best thing we could find.

00:01:08.600 --> 00:01:12.350
Jeff Portman: He didn’t see himself as disabled, 
he just saw himself as good old BilL.

00:01:12.350 --> 00:01:14.480
Tom: He loved children…

00:01:14.480 --> 00:01:16.600
Barry: And he loved the role of Santa Claus.

00:01:16.600 --> 00:01:21.500
Bill (singing): Here comes Santa Claus, 
Here comes Santa Claus, up sum saupin sleigh.

00:01:21.500 --> 00:01:25.989
Here comes Santa Claus, Here comes Santa Claus, 
up din a saupin sleigh.

00:01:25.989 --> 00:01:30.560
Jack Doepke: Bill was really a big leader 
in a movement, unbeknownst to him,

00:01:30.560 --> 00:01:34.850
of normalizing peoples’ reactions to 
people with disabilities.

00:01:36.850 --> 00:01:38.910
Bill: Please clap when I play. 

00:01:43.200 --> 00:01:45.050
Narrator: But the secrets of his past…

00:01:45.050 --> 00:01:48.100
Barry: He told me what he could about his life.

00:01:48.100 --> 00:01:53.350
That he’d been in some place that 
he doesn’t like to talk about.

00:01:53.350 --> 00:01:56.600
Narrator: Never stopped him from embracing life.

00:01:56.600 --> 00:02:00.200
Beverly Morrow: If you see pictures 
of Bill when we first met him,

00:02:00.200 --> 00:02:04.990
compared to the distinguished gentleman 
in the end, there’s quite a difference.

00:02:06.666 --> 00:02:11.350
Bill: Thank you very much ladies and gentlemen. 
It’s good to see you all, and God bless everybody.

00:02:11.350 --> 00:02:17.980
Barry: He was a little man, who made coffee 
and he played the harmonica…

00:02:17.980 --> 00:02:21.125
and that was enough.

00:02:21.125 --> 00:02:24.500
Narrator: A truly inspiring documentary

00:02:24.500 --> 00:02:28.600
about friendship, compassion, and hope. 

